msgctxt "sn35.242:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.242:0.2"
msgid "19. Āsīvisavagga"
msgstr "19. The Simile of the Vipers"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.242:0.3"
msgid "242. Dutiyadārukkhandhopamasutta"
msgstr "242. The Simile of the Tree Trunk (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.182"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: kimilāyaṃ → kimbilāyaṃ (bj, pts1) | kimmilāyaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn35.242:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kimilāyaṃ viharati gaṅgāya nadiyā tīre."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Kimibilā on the bank of the Ganges "
"river."

msgctxt "sn35.242:1.2"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho bhagavā mahantaṃ dārukkhandhaṃ gaṅgāya nadiyā sotena vuyhamānaṃ."
msgstr "Seeing a large tree trunk being carried along by the current,"

msgctxt "sn35.242:1.3"
msgid "Disvāna bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "he addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn35.242:1.4"
msgid ""
"“passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, amuṃ mahantaṃ dārukkhandhaṃ gaṅgāya nadiyā "
"sotena vuyhamānan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, do you see that large tree trunk being carried along by the "
"current of the Ganges river?”"

msgctxt "sn35.242:1.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante” … pe …"
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. …"

msgctxt "sn35.242:1.6"
msgid "evaṃ vutte, āyasmā kimilo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When this was said, Venerable Kimbila said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn35.242:1.7"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho, bhante, orimaṃ tīraṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“But sir, what’s the near shore and what’s the far shore? What’s sinking in "
"the middle? What’s getting stranded on high ground? What’s getting taken by "
"humans or non-humans? What’s getting caught up in a whirlpool? And what’s "
"rotting away?” …"

msgctxt "sn35.242:1.8"
msgid "“katamo ca, kimila, antopūtibhāvo."
msgstr "“And what, Kimbila, is rotting away?"

# See BB’s note for variants.
#. VAR: āpattiyā na vuṭṭhānaṃ → āpattiyā vuṭṭhānaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.242:1.9"
msgid ""
"Idha, kimila, bhikkhu aññataraṃ saṃkiliṭṭhaṃ āpattiṃ āpanno hoti yathārūpāya "
"āpattiyā na vuṭṭhānaṃ paññāyati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant has committed the kind of corrupt offence from which "
"there is no rehabilitation."

msgctxt "sn35.242:1.10"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, kimila, antopūtibhāvo”ti."
msgstr "This is called ‘rotting away’.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.242:1.11"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
